        <updateDate>2016-05-20T12:54:59Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong></strong> </p> <p> <p><strong>Federal Law Enforcement Self-Defense and Protection Act of 2015</strong></p> <p>This bill authorizes a federal law enforcement officer to carry a government-issued firearm during a covered furlough (i.e., a planned event during which an agency involuntarily furloughs employees due to downsizing, reduced funding, lack of work, or budget constraints including a lapse in appropriations). </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
